g.title: j1785834381
g.text: You've been patient enough with me. If you still want that story of why I left the Brittanic army... I probably owe it to you twice by now.

g.title: j3773056553
g.text: Couldn't help it, sorry. :P You were saying?

g.title: j1039691628
g.text: Everybody joins the army for a different reason. For me, I joined for... honor. For purpose.

g.title: j3776071703
g.text: I wanted to be a hero, like a Sol-damned fool.

g.title: j1725741943
g.text: Point being, I went in with big, grandiose ideas of what it meant to be a Soldier.

g.title: j3721645352
g.text: But I learned how much of a lie that really was.

g.title: j2176819379
g.text: Your role as a soldier isn't to THINK. It's to follow orders.

g.title: j3960381507
g.text: So, when I got sent in behind contested lines and told to kill all "potential enemy combatants"?

g.title: j3930033801
g.text: I did what a good soldier does. I followed orders.

g.title: j3945949356
g.text: I think I can see where this is going...

g.title: j1935953744
g.text: I don't know how many innocent lives we put in the ground that day.

g.title: j3739118338
g.text: When I went around demanding answers to why we'd just slaughtered innocents, the Brass threatened me with a dishonorable discharge.

g.title: j3047582359
g.text: Shut up. Do your job. Shoot your gun. Kill like a good soldier.

g.title: j2862403249
g.text: They were right. I shouldn't have been asking questions. I'm shit at getting to the bottom of things.

g.title: j3951729852
g.text: No, let me finish. I'M shit at getting to the bottom of a mystery. But you know who isn't?

g.title: j1091452453
g.text: And who worked as a Journo? And had connections to every major paper at the time?

g.title: j2171089510
g.text: So the deal was simple. Let me out on early retirement or the lid gets blown wide open. I wasn't important enough for them to care. They let me walk without a fuss after that.

g.title: j2837280383
g.text: So you joined the ICR after that?

g.title: j399924541
g.text: It wasn't your fault, what happened.

g.title: j3299142457
g.text: I did. And fell into exactly the same naïve trap. I trusted leadership to care about civvies.

g.title: j2586676346
g.text: If I had a pound for every time Eleanor's said that to me...

g.title: j28086728
g.text: Murder all possible infested innocents, no matter if it's true or not.

g.title: j1988801537
g.text: Have you ever tried listening to her?

g.title: j1326455914
g.text: Ooh, we could afford to put in a hot tub!

g.title: j1358673141
g.text: I just...couldn't. And neither could the rest of the Hex. And so - here we are.

g.title: j3518159758
g.text: Now you really are starting to sound like her.

g.title: j789060602
g.text: I'm sorry you've had to go through all this.

g.title: j1862554191
g.text: Doing the right thing is always the hardest choice.

g.title: j2572484087
g.text: The thing with twins, is that no matter how far away you get from them?

g.title: j499072019
g.text: They're still right there with you. Even when you're three thousand miles away behind enemy lines.

g.title: j2409914427
g.text: They find a way to weave their way into your lives.

g.title: j4276667685
g.text: Is there something else you're not telling me?

g.title: j3373627974
g.text: I'll be all right. I always am.

g.title: j2042345880
g.text: You don't have to be okay.

g.title: j2271600527
g.text: Do you... want to talk about it?

g.title: j3537288457
g.text: I appreciate that. It's a rough story. And one for another day.

g.title: j4252321457
g.text: Heh. You're right. That was bullshit. But it's a story for another day.
